cbQosServicePolicyTable.name: cbQosServicePolicyTable
cbQosServicePolicyTable.description: This table describes the interfaces/media types and the policymap that are attached to it.

cbQosServicePolicyEntry.name: cbQosServicePolicyEntry
cbQosServicePolicyEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes to which a logical interface a given policymap is attached. Depending on the interface/media type, some fields may have meaningful values, and some may not. Please see each individual descriptions.

cbQosPolicyIndex.name: cbQosPolicyIndex
cbQosPolicyIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) index for all service policies (PolicyMap that has been attached to a given logical interface).

cbQosIfType.name: cbQosIfType
cbQosIfType.description: This describes the interface/media type to which this service policy is attached.

cbQosPolicyDirection.name: cbQosPolicyDirection
cbQosPolicyDirection.description: This indicates the direction of traffic for which this service policy is applied.

cbQosIfIndex.name: cbQosIfIndex
cbQosIfIndex.description: ifIndex for the interface to which this service is attached. This field makes sense only if the logical interface has a snmp ifIndex.

cbQosFrDLCI.name: cbQosFrDLCI
cbQosFrDLCI.description: DLCI for the FRVC to which this service is attached. This field only make sense if the service policy is attached to a Frame Relay DLCI.

cbQosAtmVPI.name: cbQosAtmVPI
cbQosAtmVPI.description: VPI for the ATMVC to which this service is attached. This field only make sense if the service policy is attached to a ATM VC.

cbQosAtmVCI.name: cbQosAtmVCI
cbQosAtmVCI.description: VCI for the ATMVC to which this service is attached. This field only make sense if the service policy is attached to a ATM VC.

cbQosInterfacePolicyTable.name: cbQosInterfacePolicyTable
cbQosInterfacePolicyTable.description: This table describes the service polices that are attached to main and sub interfaces.

cbQosInterfacePolicyEntry.name: cbQosInterfacePolicyEntry
cbQosInterfacePolicyEntry.description: Using ifIndex and Direction, each unique index pair translates to a service policy that is attached to a main/sub interface, for particular traffic direction.

cbQosIFPolicyIndex.name: cbQosIFPolicyIndex
cbQosIFPolicyIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) index for all Service Policies. This is identical to cbQosPolicyIndex.

cbQosFrameRelayPolicyTable.name: cbQosFrameRelayPolicyTable
cbQosFrameRelayPolicyTable.description: This table describes the service polices that are attached to Frame Relay DLCIs.

cbQosFrameRelayPolicyEntry.name: cbQosFrameRelayPolicyEntry
cbQosFrameRelayPolicyEntry.description: Using ifIndex, FR DLCI, and Direction, each unique index combination translates to a service policy that is attached to a FR DLCI, for particular traffic direction.

cbQosFRPolicyIndex.name: cbQosFRPolicyIndex
cbQosFRPolicyIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) index for all Service Policies. This is identical to cbQosPolicyIndex.

cbQosATMPVCPolicyTable.name: cbQosATMPVCPolicyTable
cbQosATMPVCPolicyTable.description: This table describes the policies that are attached to a ATM PVC.

cbQosATMPVCPolicyEntry.name: cbQosATMPVCPolicyEntry
cbQosATMPVCPolicyEntry.description: Using ifIndex, VPI, VCI, and Direction, each unique index combination translates to a service policy that is attached to a ATM VC, for particular traffic direction.

cbQosATMPolicyIndex.name: cbQosATMPolicyIndex
cbQosATMPolicyIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) index for all Service Policies. This is identical to cbQosPolicyIndex.

cbQosObjectsTable.name: cbQosObjectsTable
cbQosObjectsTable.description: This table specifies QoS objects (classmap, policymap, match statements, and actions) hierarchy. This table also provide relationship between each PolicyIndex/ObjectsIndex pair and the ConfigIndex. ConfigIndex is essential for querying any configuration tables.

cbQosObjectsEntry.name: cbQosObjectsEntry
cbQosObjectsEntry.description: A QoS object entry. Objects covered in this table are PolicyMap, ClassMap, Match Statements, and Actions. Each entry is indexed by system-generated cbQosPolicyIndex, and cbQosObjectsIndex, which represents a runtime instance of a QoS object. In conjunction with the cbQosParentObjectsIndex, a management station can determine the hierarchical relationship of those QoS objects. Given that classmaps and service policies can be nested entites, each entry in this table represents a unique instance of such object. Each runtime object instance has a corresponding config object, which contains the configuration information of such QoS object. The config object is indexed by cbQosConfigIndex.

cbQosObjectsIndex.name: cbQosObjectsIndex
cbQosObjectsIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) instance specific index for cbQosObjectsEntry.

cbQosConfigIndex.name: cbQosConfigIndex
cbQosConfigIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) config (instance independent) index for each Object. Each objects having the same configuration share the same config index.

cbQosObjectsType.name: cbQosObjectsType
cbQosObjectsType.description: The type of the QoS object.

cbQosParentObjectsIndex.name: cbQosParentObjectsIndex
cbQosParentObjectsIndex.description: The parent instance index of a QoS object. For a ClassMap, the parent index would be the index of the attached PolicyMap. For a Match Statement, the parent index would be the index of the ClassMap that uses this Match Statement. For an action, the parent index would be the index of the ClassMap that applies such Action. For a non-hierarchical PolicyMap, the parent would be the interface to which the policy is attached, thus the parent index would be 0. For a hierarchical PolicyMap, the parent index would be the index of the ClassMap to which the nested policy is attached.

cbQosPolicyMapCfgTable.name: cbQosPolicyMapCfgTable
cbQosPolicyMapCfgTable.description: This table specifies Policymap configuration information

cbQosPolicyMapCfgEntry.name: cbQosPolicyMapCfgEntry
cbQosPolicyMapCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a policymap. The information includes: Name, and it's description. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex of each PolicyMap.

cbQosCMCfgTable.name: cbQosCMCfgTable
cbQosCMCfgTable.description: This table specifies ClassMap configuration information

cbQosCMCfgEntry.name: cbQosCMCfgEntry
cbQosCMCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a classmap. The information includes: Name, and it's description and whether it is a Mathc-All or Match-Any class. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex of each ClassMap.

cbQosCMInfo.name: cbQosCMInfo
cbQosCMInfo.description: Match all vs Match any in a given class.

cbQosMatchStmtCfgTable.name: cbQosMatchStmtCfgTable
cbQosMatchStmtCfgTable.description: This table specifies ClassMap configuration information

cbQosMatchStmtCfgEntry.name: cbQosMatchStmtCfgEntry
cbQosMatchStmtCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a MatchStatement. The information includes: Name, and whether it is a Match or Match-Not statement. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex of each MatchStatement.

cbQosMatchStmtInfo.name: cbQosMatchStmtInfo
cbQosMatchStmtInfo.description: Match vs Match Not in a given class.

cbQosQueueingCfgTable.name: cbQosQueueingCfgTable
cbQosQueueingCfgTable.description: This table specifies Queueing Action configuration information

cbQosQueueingCfgEntry.name: cbQosQueueingCfgEntry
cbQosQueueingCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a queueing action. The information includes: Bandwidth, Units, Flow Enabled, Priority Enabled, and Q size. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex of each Queueing Action.

cbQosQueueingCfgBandwidth.name: cbQosQueueingCfgBandwidth
cbQosQueueingCfgBandwidth.description: The configured bandwidth allocated to this traffic class. In the case of a bandwidth policy, this value represents a minimum b/w guarantee for the traffic class. In the case of a priority policy, this value represents the maximum rate at which priority service is guaranteed.

cbQosQueueingCfgBandwidthUnits.name: cbQosQueueingCfgBandwidthUnits
cbQosQueueingCfgBandwidthUnits.description: Units of the accompanying cbQosQueueingCfgbandwidth parameter.

cbQosQueueingCfgFlowEnabled.name: cbQosQueueingCfgFlowEnabled
cbQosQueueingCfgFlowEnabled.description: Boolean to indicate if flow-based fair-queue is enabled for this class.

cbQosQueueingCfgPriorityEnabled.name: cbQosQueueingCfgPriorityEnabled
cbQosQueueingCfgPriorityEnabled.description: Boolean to indicate if low latency queueing (priority) is enabled for this class.

cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQSize.name: cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQSize
cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQSize.description: Maximum number of packets that can be held in all the individual queues associated with this class before packets are dropped. This object is deprecated by cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQLimit.

cbQosQueueingCfgIndividualQSize.name: cbQosQueueingCfgIndividualQSize
cbQosQueueingCfgIndividualQSize.description: Maximum number of packets that can be held in an individual Flow-based fair-queue associated with this class before it drops packets (once the AggregateQSize has been reached). This field only makes sense in the context of Flow-based fair-queueing.

cbQosQueueingCfgDynamicQNumber.name: cbQosQueueingCfgDynamicQNumber
cbQosQueueingCfgDynamicQNumber.description: Number of dynamic queues supported when flow-based fair-queue is in use.

cbQosQueueingCfgPrioBurstSize.name: cbQosQueueingCfgPrioBurstSize
cbQosQueueingCfgPrioBurstSize.description: In the priority queue, this is the number of bytes allowed in a single burst. This parameter only makes sense if Priority is enabled

cbQosQueueingCfgQLimitUnits.name: cbQosQueueingCfgQLimitUnits
cbQosQueueingCfgQLimitUnits.description: Represents the unit type of cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQLimit object.

cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQLimit.name: cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQLimit
cbQosQueueingCfgAggregateQLimit.description: Maximum allowed queue size for all the individual queues associated with this class. When the queue size exceed this value, the packets will be dropped.

cbQosREDCfgTable.name: cbQosREDCfgTable
cbQosREDCfgTable.description: This table specifies WRED Action configuration information

cbQosREDCfgEntry.name: cbQosREDCfgEntry
cbQosREDCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a WRED Action. The table holds global (per traffic class) configuration like: Expon Weight and Mean Q size. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex of each WRED Action.

cbQosREDCfgExponWeight.name: cbQosREDCfgExponWeight
cbQosREDCfgExponWeight.description: The decay factor for the queue average calculation. The decay factor is equal to raising 2 to the power of N, where N could be up to 16. The smaller the number, the faster it decays.

cbQosREDCfgMeanQsize.name: cbQosREDCfgMeanQsize
cbQosREDCfgMeanQsize.description: The average queue size, computed and used by the WRED algorithm. This is deprecated by cbQosREDMeanQsize.

cbQosREDCfgDscpPrec.name: cbQosREDCfgDscpPrec
cbQosREDCfgDscpPrec.description: The Classification mechanism used by RED - precedence or DSCP-based.

cbQosREDCfgECNEnabled.name: cbQosREDCfgECNEnabled
cbQosREDCfgECNEnabled.description: Boolean to indicate if explicit congestion notification enabled for this class.

cbQosREDClassCfgTable.name: cbQosREDClassCfgTable
cbQosREDClassCfgTable.description: This table specifies WRED Action configuration information on a per IP precedence basis.

cbQosREDClassCfgEntry.name: cbQosREDClassCfgEntry
cbQosREDClassCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a WRED Action. The table holds the per IP precedence based WRED configuration parameters. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex and cbQosREDValue of each WRED Action.

cbQosREDValue.name: cbQosREDValue
cbQosREDValue.description: The IP precedence or IP DSCP of this entry.

cbQosREDCfgMinThreshold.name: cbQosREDCfgMinThreshold
cbQosREDCfgMinThreshold.description: Minimum threshold in number of packets. When the average queue length reaches this number, WRED begins to drop packets with the specified IP precedence. This is deprecated by cbQosREDClassCfgMinThreshold.

cbQosREDCfgMaxThreshold.name: cbQosREDCfgMaxThreshold
cbQosREDCfgMaxThreshold.description: Maximum threshold in number of packets. When the average queue length exceeds this number, WRED drops all packets with the specified IP precedence. This is deprecated by cbQosREDClassCfgMaxThreshold.

cbQosREDCfgPktDropProb.name: cbQosREDCfgPktDropProb
cbQosREDCfgPktDropProb.description: Denominator for the fraction of packets dropped when the average queue depth is MaxDepthThreshold. For example, if the denominator is 10, one out of every 10 packets is dropped when the average queue is at the MaxDepthThreshold.

cbQosREDClassCfgThresholdUnit.name: cbQosREDClassCfgThresholdUnit
cbQosREDClassCfgThresholdUnit.description: Represents the unit type to measure the RED thresholds. The objects covered are cbQosREDClassCfgMinThreshold and cbQosREDClassCfgMaxThreshold.

cbQosREDClassCfgMinThreshold.name: cbQosREDClassCfgMinThreshold
cbQosREDClassCfgMinThreshold.description: The minimum WRED threshold value. When the average queue length reaches this number, WRED begins to drop packets according to REDMechanism specificed in cbQosREDCfgDscpPrec.

cbQosREDClassCfgMaxThreshold.name: cbQosREDClassCfgMaxThreshold
cbQosREDClassCfgMaxThreshold.description: The maximum WRED threshold value. When the average queue length exceeds this number, WRED drops all packets according to REDMechanism specificed in cbQosREDCfgDscpPrec.

cbQosPoliceCfgTable.name: cbQosPoliceCfgTable
cbQosPoliceCfgTable.description: This table specifies Police Action configuration information.

cbQosPoliceCfgEntry.name: cbQosPoliceCfgEntry
cbQosPoliceCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a Police Action. The table holds Policy configuration parameters, such as rate, burst size, and actions based on traffic rates. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex.

cbQosPoliceCfgRate.name: cbQosPoliceCfgRate
cbQosPoliceCfgRate.description: The committed policing rate. This is the sustained rate permitted by policing. If a committed policing rate greater than 2000000000 is configurable on the system, then the configured rate is available in cbQosPoliceCfgRate64.

cbQosPoliceCfgBurstSize.name: cbQosPoliceCfgBurstSize
cbQosPoliceCfgBurstSize.description: The amount of traffic, in bytes, in excess of the committed policing rate that will be permitted by the policing feature.

cbQosPoliceCfgExtBurstSize.name: cbQosPoliceCfgExtBurstSize
cbQosPoliceCfgExtBurstSize.description: The amount of traffic, in bytes, in excess of the burst limit, which may be conditionally permitted by the policing feature. The probability that the traffic is not permitted increases as the received burst size increases.

cbQosPoliceCfgConformAction.name: cbQosPoliceCfgConformAction
cbQosPoliceCfgConformAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic is within the configured rate, that is, the traffic rate is conforming. This object is deprecated and defined in cqQosPoliceActionCfgTable.

cbQosPoliceCfgConformSetValue.name: cbQosPoliceCfgConformSetValue
cbQosPoliceCfgConformSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packets that conforms to the configured Police rate. This object is deprecated and defined in cqQosPoliceActionCfgTable.

cbQosPoliceCfgExceedAction.name: cbQosPoliceCfgExceedAction
cbQosPoliceCfgExceedAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the configured rate, that is, the traffic is non-conforming. This object is deprecated and defined in cqQosPoliceActionCfgTable.

cbQosPoliceCfgExceedSetValue.name: cbQosPoliceCfgExceedSetValue
cbQosPoliceCfgExceedSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packets that conforms to the configured Police rate. This object is deprecated and defined in cqQosPoliceActionCfgTable.

cbQosPoliceCfgViolateAction.name: cbQosPoliceCfgViolateAction
cbQosPoliceCfgViolateAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the conform and exceed token buckets. This object is deprecated and defined in cqQosPoliceActionCfgTable.

cbQosPoliceCfgViolateSetValue.name: cbQosPoliceCfgViolateSetValue
cbQosPoliceCfgViolateSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packets that conforms to the Police violate action. The packet attibute values depend on the action that is taken for the particular packet. For example, if the action was to set the dscp value, this entry describes the value it is set to. This object is deprecated and defined in cqQosPoliceActionCfgTable.

cbQosPoliceCfgPir.name: cbQosPoliceCfgPir
cbQosPoliceCfgPir.description: The committed policing rate. This is the peak rate permitted by two rate policing.

cbQosPoliceCfgRate64.name: cbQosPoliceCfgRate64
cbQosPoliceCfgRate64.description: The committed policing rate. This is the sustained rate permitted by policing.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgTable.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgTable
cbQosPoliceActionCfgTable.description: This table specifies Police Action configuration information.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgEntry.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgEntry
cbQosPoliceActionCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about Actions for one Police. The table holds Polic action specific configuration parameters. This table is a sub-table for cbQosPoliceCfgTable. There is a 1-to-1 association between one entry here and one entry in cbQosPoliceCfgTable. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. This table has two indices. The first is cbQosConfigIndex which is drived directly from cbQosPoliceCfgTable to keep the 1-to-1 mapping nature between two tables. The second is cbQosPoliceActionCfgIndex used to reference the actual actions configured. The maximum number of actions supported is determined by the system, which is 5 currently.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgIndex.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgIndex
cbQosPoliceActionCfgIndex.description: An arbitrary (system-assigned) index for police actions that are defined by a police configuration.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgConform.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgConform
cbQosPoliceActionCfgConform.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the conform and exceed token buckets.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgConformSetValue.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgConformSetValue
cbQosPoliceActionCfgConformSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packet set by police action defined in cbQosPoliceActionCfgConform. This object will be set to zero if the corrsponding police action does not require a set value, such as no action, drop action or transmit action.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceed.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceed
cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceed.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the conform and exceed token buckets.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceedSetValue.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceedSetValue
cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceedSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packet set by police action defined in cbQosPoliceActionCfgExceed. This object will be set to zero if the corrsponding police action does not require a set value, such as no action, drop action or transmit action.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolate.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolate
cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolate.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the conform and exceed token buckets.

cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolateSetValue.name: cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolateSetValue
cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolateSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packet set by police action defined in cbQosPoliceActionCfgViolate. This object will be set to zero if the corrsponding police action does not require a set value, such as no action, drop action or transmit action.

cbQosTSCfgTable.name: cbQosTSCfgTable
cbQosTSCfgTable.description: This table specifies traffic-shaping Action configuration information.

cbQosTSCfgEntry.name: cbQosTSCfgEntry
cbQosTSCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a traffic-shaping Action. The table holds Traffic Shaping configuration parameters, such as rate, burst size, and Shaping types. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex.

cbQosTSCfgRate.name: cbQosTSCfgRate
cbQosTSCfgRate.description: The committed traffic-shaping rate. This is the sustained rate permitted by the traffic-shaping.

cbQosTSCfgBurstSize.name: cbQosTSCfgBurstSize
cbQosTSCfgBurstSize.description: The amount of traffic, in bits, in excess of the committed traffic-shaping rate that will be instantaneously permitted by this feature.

cbQosTSCfgExtBurstSize.name: cbQosTSCfgExtBurstSize
cbQosTSCfgExtBurstSize.description: The amount of traffic, in bits, in excess of the burst limit, which may be conditionnally permitted by traffic-shaping feature.

cbQosTSCfgAdaptiveEnabled.name: cbQosTSCfgAdaptiveEnabled
cbQosTSCfgAdaptiveEnabled.description: This object indicates is adaptive traffic-shaping has been enabled.

cbQosTSCfgAdaptiveRate.name: cbQosTSCfgAdaptiveRate
cbQosTSCfgAdaptiveRate.description: This object represents the current adaptive traffic shaping rate.

cbQosTSCfgLimitType.name: cbQosTSCfgLimitType
cbQosTSCfgLimitType.description: This object indicates if traffic-shaping is limiting traffic based on the peak rate or the average rate.

cbQosSetCfgTable.name: cbQosSetCfgTable
cbQosSetCfgTable.description: This table specifies Packet Marking Action configuration information.

cbQosSetCfgEntry.name: cbQosSetCfgEntry
cbQosSetCfgEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes configuration information about a Packet Marking Action. The table holds Packet Marking configuration parameters, such as type of packet marking and values being set to. This table contains configuration information only, no statistics associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the cbQosConfigIndex.

cbQosSetCfgFeature.name: cbQosSetCfgFeature
cbQosSetCfgFeature.description: The bit-wise position of each packet marking feature.

cbQosSetCfgIpDSCPValue.name: cbQosSetCfgIpDSCPValue
cbQosSetCfgIpDSCPValue.description: The IP DSCP value at which the packet is being set by the packet marking feature.

cbQosSetCfgIpPrecedenceValue.name: cbQosSetCfgIpPrecedenceValue
cbQosSetCfgIpPrecedenceValue.description: The IP precedence value at which the packet is being set by the packet marking feature.

cbQosSetCfgQosGroupValue.name: cbQosSetCfgQosGroupValue
cbQosSetCfgQosGroupValue.description: The QoS Group number at which the packet is being set by the packet marking feature.

cbQosSetCfgL2CosValue.name: cbQosSetCfgL2CosValue
cbQosSetCfgL2CosValue.description: The Layer 2 Cos value at which the packet is being set by the packet marking feature.

cbQosSetCfgMplsExpValue.name: cbQosSetCfgMplsExpValue
cbQosSetCfgMplsExpValue.description: The MPLS experimental value at which the packet is being set by the packet marking feature.

cbQosSetCfgDiscardClassValue.name: cbQosSetCfgDiscardClassValue
cbQosSetCfgDiscardClassValue.description: The Discard Class value at which the packet is being set by the packet marking feature.

cbQosCMStatsTable.name: cbQosCMStatsTable
cbQosCMStatsTable.description: This table specifies ClassMap related Statistical information.

cbQosCMStatsEntry.name: cbQosCMStatsEntry
cbQosCMStatsEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes the statistical information about ClassMap. ClassMap specific information you can find in this table are : pre/post policy pkt/byte counts, bit rates, drop pkt/bytes and no buffer drops. This table contains statistical information only, no configuration information associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the instance specific IDs, such as cbQosPolicyIndex and cbQosObjectsIndex.

cbQosCMPrePolicyPktOverflow.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyPktOverflow
cbQosCMPrePolicyPktOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits count of inbound packets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPrePolicyPkt.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyPkt
cbQosCMPrePolicyPkt.description: The lower 32 bits count of inbound packets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPrePolicyPkt64.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyPkt64
cbQosCMPrePolicyPkt64.description: The 64 bits count of inbound packets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPrePolicyByteOverflow.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyByteOverflow
cbQosCMPrePolicyByteOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits count of inbound octets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPrePolicyByte.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyByte
cbQosCMPrePolicyByte.description: The lower 32 bits count of inbound octets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPrePolicyByte64.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyByte64
cbQosCMPrePolicyByte64.description: The 64 bits count of inbound octets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPrePolicyBitRate.name: cbQosCMPrePolicyBitRate
cbQosCMPrePolicyBitRate.description: The bit rate of the traffic prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosCMPostPolicyByteOverflow.name: cbQosCMPostPolicyByteOverflow
cbQosCMPostPolicyByteOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits count of outbound octets after executing QoS policies.

cbQosCMPostPolicyByte.name: cbQosCMPostPolicyByte
cbQosCMPostPolicyByte.description: The lower 32 bits count of outbound octets after executing QoS policies.

cbQosCMPostPolicyByte64.name: cbQosCMPostPolicyByte64
cbQosCMPostPolicyByte64.description: The 64 bits count of outbound octets after executing QoS policies.

cbQosCMPostPolicyBitRate.name: cbQosCMPostPolicyBitRate
cbQosCMPostPolicyBitRate.description: The bit rate of the traffic after executing QoS policies.

cbQosCMDropPktOverflow.name: cbQosCMDropPktOverflow
cbQosCMDropPktOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits counter of dropped pkts per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMDropPkt.name: cbQosCMDropPkt
cbQosCMDropPkt.description: The lower 32 bits counter of dropped pkts per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMDropPkt64.name: cbQosCMDropPkt64
cbQosCMDropPkt64.description: The 64 bits counter of dropped pkts per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMDropByteOverflow.name: cbQosCMDropByteOverflow
cbQosCMDropByteOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits counter of dropped bytes per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMDropByte.name: cbQosCMDropByte
cbQosCMDropByte.description: The lower 32 bits counter of dropped bytes per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMDropByte64.name: cbQosCMDropByte64
cbQosCMDropByte64.description: The 64 bits counter of dropped bytes per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMDropBitRate.name: cbQosCMDropBitRate
cbQosCMDropBitRate.description: The bit rate of the drops per class as the result of all features that can produce drops (e.g., police, random detect, etc.).

cbQosCMNoBufDropPktOverflow.name: cbQosCMNoBufDropPktOverflow
cbQosCMNoBufDropPktOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits drop packet count which occured due to a lack of SRAM buffers during output processing on an interface.

cbQosCMNoBufDropPkt.name: cbQosCMNoBufDropPkt
cbQosCMNoBufDropPkt.description: The lower 32 bits drop packet count which occured due to a lack of SRAM buffers during output processing on an interface.

cbQosCMNoBufDropPkt64.name: cbQosCMNoBufDropPkt64
cbQosCMNoBufDropPkt64.description: The 64 bits drop packet count which occured due to a lack of SRAM buffers during output processing on an interface.

cbQosMatchStmtStatsTable.name: cbQosMatchStmtStatsTable
cbQosMatchStmtStatsTable.description: This table specifies Match Statement related statistical information.

cbQosMatchStmtStatsEntry.name: cbQosMatchStmtStatsEntry
cbQosMatchStmtStatsEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes the statistical information about Match Statement. Match Statement specific information you can find in this table are : Pre policy pkt/byte counters, and bit rates. This table contains statistical information only, no configuration information associated with it. Therefore, it is indexed by the instance specific IDs, such as cbQosPolicyIndex and cbQosObjectsIndex.

cbQosMatchPrePolicyPktOverflow.name: cbQosMatchPrePolicyPktOverflow
cbQosMatchPrePolicyPktOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits count of inbound packets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosMatchPrePolicyPkt.name: cbQosMatchPrePolicyPkt
cbQosMatchPrePolicyPkt.description: The lower 32 bits count of inbound packets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosMatchPrePolicyPkt64.name: cbQosMatchPrePolicyPkt64
cbQosMatchPrePolicyPkt64.description: The 64 bits count of inbound packets prior to executing any QoS policies.

cbQosMatchPrePolicyByteOverflow.name: cbQosMatchPrePolicyByteOverflow
cbQosMatchPrePolicyByteOverflow.description: The upper 32 bits count of inbound octets prior to executing any QoS policies.
